  "response": "Starting an eSports organization requires several key steps:\n\n1. Define Your Focus\n- Choose specific games/genres\n- Determine team size and structure\n- Identify target competitive levels\n\n2. Legal Setup\n- Register your organization\n- Create a business plan\n- Establish legal structure (LLC, etc.)\n- Open business bank account\n\n3. Financial Planning\n- Secure initial funding\n- Determine revenue streams\n- Create budget for team expenses\n- Consider sponsorships and investments\n\n4. Team Recruitment\n- Scout talented players\n- Conduct tryouts\n- Build team chemistry\n- Create contracts and expectations\n\n5. Infrastructure\n- Create team branding\n- Design logos and uniforms\n- Build social media presence\n- Set up communication platforms\n\n6. Competitive Strategy\n- Register for tournaments\n- Determine competition schedule\n- Invest in training resources\n- Hire coaches/managers\n\n7. Marketing and Promotion\n- Create website\n- Develop social media strategy\n- Stream team activities\n- Engage with fan community\n\n8. Operational Considerations\n- Provide player support\n- Establish team performance standards\n- Create professional development opportunities\n- Manage team finances\n\n9. Network and Grow\n- Attend eSports events\n- Build industry connections\n- Continuously improve team performance",
